<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-675-380  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 675 380.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  July 16 1990 n475 p10(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Integration crossroads: McDonnell's SI unit might face cost cuts.andO;(McDonnell Douglas Systems Integration Co.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Moore, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>McDonnell Douglas Systems Integration Co is implementing acost-cutting plan that should decrease the company's coststructure by $700 million a year but will mean substantiallayoffs.andP;  Industry observers suggest that the plan may indicatethe divestment of the systems integration division, the onlydomestic computer operation left after an 18-month effort byDouglas Aircraft Co to sell off its information technologybusinesses.andP;  McDonnell Douglas could sell off some of its softwareproducts, which include geographic information systems,computer-aided software engineering and computer-aideddesign/computer-aided manufacturing (CAD/CAM) software.andP;  Anargument against selling off the software is that the division isprofitable in its present state and should not be alteredneedlessly.andP;  McDonnell Douglas Systems Integration has also beguna major integration project for its parent company.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   McDonnell Douglas Corp. McDonnell Douglas Systems Integration Co.andO;(costs).andO;Topic:     LayoffCost of OperationComputer Systems IntegratorsSoftware PackagesBusiness PlanningDivestment.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>